fielddes: ID of the Establishment; an Establishment is distinct based on a combination of Legal Entity and USPS validated address.
Unique ID assigned by BQ to the Organization.

Primary name of the Organization, derived from multiple sources including the IRS, Dept. of Labor, SEC, SBA, and local jurisdictions. A waterfall is in place to pick the Organization's primary name, with preference given to IRS related sources.
TICKER of the Organization if it is publicly listed.

Link to the Organization's primary website. A company's website is not usually included in the regulatory filings, but BQ uses alternative methods to identify these links, which may result in occasional inaccuracies.
Unique ID of the Legal Entity. A Legal Entity is part of an Organization and is registered with the Secretary of State of a jurisdiction.
Name of the Legal Entity operating the Establishment
Jurisdiction code (2-digit state name) in which the Legal Entity is registered, typically with the Secretary of State.
Unique number issued by the jurisdiction with which the Legal Entity is registered.
ID of the Immediate Parent if the Legal Entity is a child.
Classification that indicates whether address of the Establishment is a registered address, non-registered address, or officer address
Indicator that equals 1 if the Establishment address is valid based on a match with the USPS address verification and 0 otherwise.
1st line of the Establishment's address. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
2nd line of the Establishment's address, such as a unit or suite number. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
City of the Establishment's address. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
State abbreviation of the Establishment's address. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
State name of the Establishment's address. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
County-level FIPS code of the Establishment's address. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
County name of the Establishment's address. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
Country of the Establishment's address. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
5-digit zip code of the Establishment's address. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
9-digit zip code (ZIP + 4) of the Establishment's address. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
Zip code classification of the Establishment's address stating whether it is a P.O. Box or not. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
Latitude of the Establishment's address. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
Longitude of the Establishment's address. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
Classification that indicates whether the Establishment's address is Match-Mailable or Non-Mailable based on USPS reporting.
RDI indicates whether the Establishment's address is Residential, Commercial, P.O. Box and Unknown based on USPS reporting.

The Core-Based Statistical Area (CBSA) is a 5-digit numeric code which identifies the Metropolitan Statistical Area or Micropolitan Statistical Area in which the Establishment's address lies according to USPS.
Name of the Core-Based Statistical Area (CBSA) which identifies the Metropolitan Statistical Area or Micropolitan Statistical Area in which the Establishment's address lies according to USPS.
Metro or Micro Type classification of the Core-Based Statistical Area (CBSA) in which the Establihment's  address lies according to USPS.
Numerical portion (if any) of the 2nd line of the Establishment's address, such as a unit or suite number. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
Indicator that equals 1 if the Establishment's address is the "default" address for a building ( i.e., the main lobby) and 0 otherwise. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
Indicator that states "Yes" if the Establishment's  address is verified to be deliverable based on the Delivery Point Validation Process of USPS.
Congressional District Code of the Establishment's address. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
